🔹 Membership Operators in Python

Membership operators are used to check whether a value exists inside a sequence such as a list, tuple, string, or set.

👉 Types of Membership Operators:

1. in operator
Returns True if the value is present in the sequence.


2. not in operator
Returns True if the value is NOT present in the sequence.




---

✅ Examples:

# Example with list
numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

print(3 in numbers)       # True
print(10 in numbers)      # False
print(10 not in numbers)  # True

# Example with string
text = "Python"

print("P" in text)        # True
print("z" not in text)    # True


---

📌 Use Cases:

Checking if an element exists in a list

Validating user input

Searching data in collections
